=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">καλεῖται ὁ αὐτὸς καὶ ἔ. καὶ θίασος</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0008.tlg001.perseus-grc1:8:362e\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ath.\">Ath.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">8.362e</biblScope> </bibl> </cit> ; functioning as a <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">friendly society,</tr_> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Plin.\">Plin.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">Ep.Trai.</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">92</biblScope> </bibl> ; it could apparently lend to a non-member, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ὅρος χωρίων ὑποκειμένων τῷ ἐ. καὶ τῷ ἀρχεράνῳ</quote_> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ SIG\">SIG</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1198</biblScope> </bibl> </cit> (Amorgos, <date TEIform=\"date\">iii B. C.</date>), cf. <bibl n=\"http://www.trismegistos.org/text/18577\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ BGU\">BGU</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1133</biblScope> </bibl>-<bibl n=\"http://www.trismegistos.org/text/9103\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">6</biblScope> </bibl> <date TEIform=\"date\">(i B. C.)</date>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}